   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3737_1.jpg"/>

            <opener>

               <dateline>
                  <date when="1918-09-30">30 Sept. 1918</date>
               </dateline>
               <address rend="letterhead">
                  <addrLine>THE LODGE,</addrLine>
                  <addrLine><del>KING'S</del><add place="inline">ETON</add> COLLEGE</addrLine>
                  <!-- Need to indicate that this has been added in pen, not letterhead -->
                  <addrLine>
                     <del>CAMBRIDGE.</del>
                  </addrLine>
               </address>


               <salute>My dear Mr Hardy</salute>

            </opener>

            <p>My very best thanks to you and to <persName ref="#ps:FlorenceHardy">Mrs
                  Hardy</persName> for your very kind thought in writing. I value your good wishes
               most highly.</p>

            <p>I should like to think that some day in spring or summer next might find you inclined
               to visit <placeName ref="#pl:EtonCollege">the Eton Lodge</placeName> &amp; give me
               the pleasure of showing you <pb n="2" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3737_2.jpg"/> one of the most
               beautiful places in <placeName ref="#pl:England">England</placeName>. </p>

            <closer>

               <salute>Yours very sincerely</salute>
               <signed>M. R. James</signed>

            </closer>




         </div>
      </body>
